HEADWORD: Loculus
<hw>Loc"u*lus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Loculi</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., little place, a
compartment.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the
spaces between the septa in the Anthozoa.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>One of the compartments of a
several-celled ovary; loculament.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Locum tenens</ent>⟦br⟧
